  "prompt": "How do I disclose Interest free perpetual loan given by a parent to subsidiary as per Indian GAAPs in the companies of both, parent and subsidary?",
  "response": "Under Indian Generally Accepted Accounting Principles (GAAP), the disclosure of an interest-free perpetual loan from a parent company to its subsidiary must be handled carefully in the financial statements of both entities. Here\u2019s a general guideline on how to approach this:\n\n### For the Parent Company:\n\n1. **Classification**: \n   - The loan should be classified as an investment in the subsidiary in the parent company's financial statements, as it represents a form of financial support to the subsidiary.\n\n2. **Disclosure in Notes to Accounts**: \n   - The parent company should include a note in the financial statements detailing the nature of the transaction. Include the following specifics:\n     - The amount of the interest-free perpetual loan given to the subsidiary.\n     - Mention that the loan is perpetual and does not have a specified repayment period.\n     - Clarify that the loan is interest-free, indicating the terms of the agreement.\n     - Discuss any conditions or covenants if applicable.\n\n### For the Subsidiary Company:\n\n1. **Classification**: \n   - The loan should be classified as a long-term liability, as it is a loan advanced to the subsidiary by the parent. Since it is perpetual, clarify that it does not have a fixed repayment date.\n\n2. **Disclosure in Notes to Accounts**: \n   - Include a note regarding the interest-free perpetual loan. The contents of the note could include:\n     - The total amount of the loan received from the parent company.\n     - The nature of the loan (interest-free and perpetual).\n     - Any obligations or restrictions that the subsidiary must comply with because of the loan, if applicable.\n\n3. **Impact on Financial Ratios**: \n   - In some cases, since the loan is classified as a liability, it may affect certain financial ratios (like debt-to-equity ratios). Therefore, it should be confirmed that this is clearly communicated in the management discussion and analysis section of the financial statements if necessary.\n\n### Important Considerations:\n\n- **Regulatory Compliance**: Ensure that any disclosure meets the regulatory requirements set out by the Companies Act, 2013 and other relevant regulations.\n  \n- **Transfer Pricing Implications**: Since the loan is interest-free, it may be subject to transfer pricing regulations. Ensure compliance and proper documentation to justify the interest-free nature of the loan.\n\nBy following these guidelines, both companies can adhere to Indian GAAPs in disclosing the interest-free perpetual loan appropriately in their financial statements.",
